itational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Hywel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name. Some write the name Hoel, which they render 'lordly;' if so, it may come from huail, a vice-regent, regent. Arthur derives the surname Howell from Corn. -Brit, houl, the sun; and he adds, high, exalted.' But Hywel is rather from hywel, conspicuous."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Yevan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the Welsh surname, a shortened form of the patronymic <i>ap Evan</i> ‘son of Evan’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Yevan ap Hywel was born about 1245, in Llechryd, Cardiganshire, Wales, his father, Howel ap Sitsylit, was 57 and his mother, Gwladys ferch Morgan Fychan of Avan Wallia, was 35. He had at least 1 son with Jenet verch Jeven. He died about 1290, in Cardiganshire, Wales, at the age of 47."},"et":{"about 1245–about 1290":"umbes 1245–umbes 1290","1245–1290":"1245–1290","1250–1290":"1250–1290","1290–1320":"1290–1320","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1212–Female":"1212–Surnud","1190":"1190","about 1290":"umbes 1290","1212":"1212","1245":"1245","1320":"1320","about 1245":"umbes 1245","1250":"1250","1290":"1290","Llechryd, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Llechryd, Cardiganshire, Wales","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1245–about 1290":"noin 1245–noin 1290","1245–1290":"1245–1290","1250–1290":"1250–1290","1290–1320":"1290–1320","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1212–Female":"1212–Kuollut","1190":"1190","about 1290":"noin 1290","1212":"1212","1245":"1245","1320":"1320","about